                "text": "`catalog.New` normalizes each product's `Tags` by calling `normalizedTags`.\n\nExactly what it does:\n\n- Does not trim whitespace.\n- Does not lowercase tags.\n- Removes empty string tags: `\"\"`.\n- Deduplicates exact string matches.\n- Does not preserve input order.\n- Sorts the remaining tags lexicographically with `sort.Strings`.\n\nSo for example:\n\n```go\ncatalog.New(catalog.Product{\n    Tags: []string{\" Fresh \", \"fresh\", \"\", \"cold\", \"fresh\"},\n})\n```\n\nwould store tags as:\n\n```go\n[]string{\" Fresh \", \"cold\", \"fresh\"}\n```\n\nAlso, if the input tag slice is empty or nil, the stored `Tags` becomes `nil`.",
